1. Implicit Type Casting (Widening / Automatic)

- Happens automatically
- When converting a smaller type to a larger type
- No data loss

Example:

int a = 10;
double b = a; 
System.out.println(b);


2. Explicit Type Casting (Narrowing / Manual)

- Done manually by the programmer
- When converting a larger type to a smaller type
- Possible data loss

Example:

double x = 10.75;
int y = (int) x; 
System.out.println(y);
